						<summary>

						<p>In a field called Maṭṭan-kaṭṭe.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Mallikārjuna 1455 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is a badly worn out record. It states that Panḍaridēva voḍeya was governing the Bārakūru-rājya under the orders of Timmaṇa-daṇāyaka when Mallikārjuna was ruling over the empire from the capital Vijayanagara. It seems to record some grants which were entrusted to the care of Gaṇapu-setti. The details of which are lost.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1377, Yuva, Jyēshṭha, ba. 1 Sunday corresponding to 1455 A.D., June 1, Sunday.</p>						

						</summary>
